<h3>What is Mozharness?</h3>
<ul>
<li>Semi-official definition<br />
  <ul>
    <blockquote><i>
Mozharness is a configuration-driven script harness with full logging that allows production infrastructure and individual developers to use the same scripts.
    </i></blockquote>
  </ul>
  <ul><li class="monospace">
configuration-driven
  </li><li class="monospace">
script harness
  </li><li class="monospace">
full logging
  </li><li class="monospace">
sharing
</li></ul></li>
<li>
Bare bones:
  <ul><li>
A harness to write + run python scripts. Or,
  </li><li>
A python script harness.
  </li><ul><li>
<a href="https://encrypted.google.com/search?q=script%20harness">https://encrypted.google.com/search?q=script harness</a> : lots of "test harness" results
    </li><li class="monospace">
<a href="https://encrypted.google.com/search?q=%22script+harness%22">https://encrypted.google.com/search?q="script+harness"</a> : Mozharness is #5.
    </li><li>
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_harness">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test_harness</a> : "test harness" has its own Wikipedia page.
    </li><li class="monospace">
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?search=script+harness">https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?search=script+harness</a> : "script harness" doesn't.
    </li></ul>
  </li></ul>
</ul>

<p>
<a href="02-why.html">why --&gt;</a><br />
</p>

</body></html>
